@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title The Mathematics of Failure Certainty

' [step1 {"name":"Single Node Reliability"}]
rectangle "Single Node" as node1 #LightBlue
note right of node1
  Daily probability of failure (**p**)
  e.g., p = 0.001 (1 in 1000 days)
end note
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Survival Probability"}]
rectangle "Survival" as survival #LightGreen
node1 -> survival
note right of survival
  Probability of **not** failing today:
  **1 - p**
  e.g., 0.999 (99.9%)
end note
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Cluster Reliability (N Nodes)"}]
rectangle "The Cluster (N = 10,000)" as cluster #AliceBlue
survival -> cluster
note right of cluster
  Probability that **all** nodes survive:
  **(1 - p)^N**
  e.g., (0.999)^10,000 ≈ 0.000045
end note
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"The Certainty of Failure"}]
rectangle "System Failure Probability" as system #FFCCCC
cluster -> system
note right of system #Salmon
  Probability of **at least one** failure:
  **P = 1 - (1 - p)^N**
  For 10,000 nodes: **P = 99.995%**
end note
' [/step4]

' [step5 {"name":"The Core Insight"}]
rectangle "Core Insight\nFailure at scale is not an if,\nit is a when.\nSoftware must tolerate\ncomponent death as normal." as insight #E6F3FF
system -> insight
' [/step5]

@enduml
